                                        <comments>
                            <comment id="12595364" author="mikedd" created="Thu, 8 May 2008 19:55:39 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Looks like this is true for Informix 9.3 as well (which is the oldest version supported by OpenJPA). From the SQL guide (page 4-46) the syntax looks something like this : &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;CREATE TABLE [database@&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;dbservername&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;]:&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;schemaname&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;.tablename . . .&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="12595377" author="dinkar" created="Thu, 8 May 2008 21:05:58 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;In this patch, I took out the override for catalogSeparator, so it will default to &quot;dot&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12595396" author="ppoddar@apache.org" created="Thu, 8 May 2008 22:26:36 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;The properties of a database dictionary are highly configurable and hence the following persistence.xml configuration may attain the the same effect without any code change&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;      &amp;lt;property name=&quot;openjpa.jdbc.DBDictionary&quot; value=&quot;informix(CatalogSeparator=&apos;.&apos;&quot;)/&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12596145" author="pcl" created="Mon, 12 May 2008 19:05:28 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Applied to 1.1.x branch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12735767" author="fyrewyld" created="Mon, 27 Jul 2009 21:47:50 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Built a version of the patch for &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OPENJPA-594&quot; title=&quot;Incorrect schema separator used for Informix tables&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;OPENJPA-594&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;OPENJPA-594&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; for 1.0.x&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
